	<logo>https://static.globalissues.org/i/globalissues/logo-feed.jpg</logo><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40204</id><title>Climate and Health: Urgent Need for Adaptation Strategies in Africa</title><updated>2025-06-20T11:15:59-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40204" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://static.globalissues.org/ips/2025/06/IMG_2960-629x231.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://static.globalissues.org/ips/2025/06/IMG_2960-629x231.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;BONN, Jun 20 (IPS)  - In recent years, there has been growing evidence of how climate change is impacting human health in several ways.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40204&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “Climate and Health: Urgent Need for Adaptation Strategies in Africa”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://static.globalissues.org/ips/2025/06/IMG_2960-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40207</id><title>Women Protestors Targeted, Insulted on Georgian Anti-Government Rallies</title><updated>2025-06-20T09:02:30-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40207" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://static.globalissues.org/ips/2025/06/1000013396-354x472.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://static.globalissues.org/ips/2025/06/1000013396-354x472.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;BRATISLAVA, Jun 20 (IPS)  - Having attended hundreds of anti-government protests in the Georgian capital, Tbilisi, Gvantsa Kalandadze is no stranger to police intimidation and violence.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40207&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “Women Protestors Targeted, Insulted on Georgian Anti-Government Rallies”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://static.globalissues.org/ips/2025/06/1000013396-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40213</id><title>Ukraine: Security Council hears of escalating attacks, diplomatic developments</title><updated>2025-06-20T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40213" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/24-04-2025-Kyiv-Ukraine-attacks-08.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/24-04-2025-Kyiv-Ukraine-attacks-08.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The UN Security Council met on Friday to discuss the situation in Ukraine, where intensified fighting continues, affecting new areas and prompting further displacement. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40213&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “Ukraine: Security Council hears of escalating attacks, diplomatic developments”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/24-04-2025-Kyiv-Ukraine-attacks-08.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40212</id><title>‘A fire no one can control’: UN warns of spiralling Iran-Israel war</title><updated>2025-06-20T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40212" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/20-06-2025-UN-Photo-Guterres-01.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/20-06-2025-UN-Photo-Guterres-01.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The world stands on the edge of catastrophe, United Nations Secretary-General António Guterres warned on Friday, as Israel’s military campaign inside Iran intensifies and strikes on nuclear facilities threaten to trigger a catastrophe.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40212&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “‘A fire no one can control’: UN warns of spiralling Iran-Israel war”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/20-06-2025-UN-Photo-Guterres-01.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40211</id><title>UN Peacebuilding Commission ‘more needed than ever’ amid rising conflict</title><updated>2025-06-20T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40211" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/08-05-2020-NICA-750383-UNMIL-Chinese-FPU.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/08-05-2020-NICA-750383-UNMIL-Chinese-FPU.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Former Liberian President Ellen Johnson-Sirleaf and other senior officials from across the world have spoken about how international support was critical to putting their countries on the path to peace.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40211&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “UN Peacebuilding Commission ‘more needed than ever’ amid rising conflict”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/08-05-2020-NICA-750383-UNMIL-Chinese-FPU.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40210</id><title>WHO warns of a health financing emergency</title><updated>2025-06-20T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40210" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/28-02-2025-UNAIDS-Tanzania-02.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/28-02-2025-UNAIDS-Tanzania-02.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The world is facing a health financing emergency, according to Dr. Kalipso Chalkidou, Director for Health Financing and Economics for the World Health Organization (WHO).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40210&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “WHO warns of a health financing emergency”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/28-02-2025-UNAIDS-Tanzania-02.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40209</id><title>For too long, ‘unbound horrors’ have unfolded in Sudan</title><updated>2025-06-20T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40209" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/21-04-2025-UNICEF-Sudan-16.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/21-04-2025-UNICEF-Sudan-16.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Hostilities continue to escalate across Sudan’s North Darfur and Kordofan regions, with reports of civilian casualties, sexual violence, abductions and looting, the UN human rights chief warned on Friday, describing the consequences as disastrous.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40209&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “For too long, ‘unbound horrors’ have unfolded in Sudan”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/21-04-2025-UNICEF-Sudan-16.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40208</id><title>From Syria, UN refugee chief calls for greater solidarity with displaced people</title><updated>2025-06-20T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40208" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/19-06-2025-UNHCR-Venezuelan-refugees.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/19-06-2025-UNHCR-Venezuelan-refugees.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Although record numbers of people – over 122 million worldwide – have been uprooted due to war, violence and persecution, their ability to find safety and support is threatened more than ever. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40208&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “From Syria, UN refugee chief calls for greater solidarity with displaced people”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/19-06-2025-UNHCR-Venezuelan-refugees.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40206</id><title>Gaza horrors continue as the weakest succumb to injuries and disease</title><updated>2025-06-20T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40206" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/30-05-2025-UNICEF-Gaza-08.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/30-05-2025-UNICEF-Gaza-08.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Death and suffering in Gaza are ever-present and the enclave&#039;s people now have little choice but to risk their lives to fetch aid supplies, UN agencies said on Friday. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40206&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “Gaza horrors continue as the weakest succumb to injuries and disease”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/30-05-2025-UNICEF-Gaza-08.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40205</id><title>MIDDLE EAST CRISIS LIVE: 'Give peace a chance' UN chief urges Israel and Iran</title><updated>2025-06-20T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40205" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/15-05-2025_WHO_Gaza.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/15-05-2025_WHO_Gaza.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;One week since the Israel-Iran conflict erupted, diplomatic efforts to end the war are ramping up in Geneva as foreign ministers from France, Germany, the UK and the EU prepare to meet their Iranian counterpart. In New York, meanwhile, the UN Security Council just heard the UN Secretary-General warn ambassadors that “we are on course to chaos” if the war widens “which could ignite a fire that no one can can control.” We&#039;ll be covering these developments including updates from Gaza. UN News app users can follow here.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/20/40205&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “MIDDLE EAST CRISIS LIVE: &#039;Give peace a chance&#039; UN chief urges Israel and Iran”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/15-05-2025_WHO_Gaza.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry></feed><!-- 0.0013s -->